de amicorum sententia] ‘Pursuant to the opinion of his friends,' a common for- mula. It was Roman practice to invite friends to be present, to give their advice on many important occasions, and to serve as witnesses afterwards, if there should be need.

C. Caesaris] Caesar, as Pontifex Maxi- mus, had an official residence in the Via Sacra, as Suetonius says (Julius, c. 46). It was in a frequented part of Rome (celebri loco). See Vol. i., Index, Celeber.
